The paper deals with the application of recurrent neural networks for classifying process instances. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with event log traces, which are commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper deals with improving the training time of the classification model, which could be relevant to the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
